review_blob:
Bottle.
Minimal aroma despite a lot of head on the pour. Fairly hazy pour but goes down very smoothly and doesnt taste like 9.5% ABV. Taste of clove and fruits, slight apple flavor it seemed.
Very good beer overall

Tap
Minimal aroma I thought. Pours a very dark brown, almost a molasses color. Superb taste, sweet flavor and strong hints of bourbon and vanilla. Fantastic flavor that drinks very smoothly despite being quite boozy at 13.4%.
Hoping to find it elsewhere.

Bottle. I expected a lot more from this beer, I have to say.  No aroma to speak of.  Golden hue which is surprisingly clear and minimal head, if any, which disappears almost instantly.  You get a hint of the lemon and orange but the citrus flavor is actually a bit underwhelming - again, I expected much better.
beer_name: Blue Moon Spring Blonde Wheat Ale

review_blob: On Tap. Overall, its a great great beer.  Maybe a little too coffee-y for me, but still a great beer.  Good aroma of oak and coffee.  Pitch black color with a brownish head which persisted for a bit.  Strong flavor of coffee and oats, though it did rather stick on the palate a bit too long for me.  Thats really the one complaint I have with this fantastic beer.
Tap. Hamms is simply awful, its a low quality American lager. Id much rather a Miller/Bud Lite.

Tap & Bottle. Complex, oaky aroma with chocolate and caramel aspects.  Pitch black beer with a small, light brown head which didnt last too long. Amazinig taste, complex with chocolate, caramel, a good roast to it all. Not as heavy as one might expect, and the flavor sticks on your tongue which is very welcome.  Simply fantastic

Bottle. Bit of a standard aroma,. Yellowish hue, somewhat hazy, small white head disappeared quickly. Hoppy citrus flavor, good wheat beer flavor. Goes down smoothly, no bitterness, taste disappears somewhat quickly. Good wheat beer, always enjoy a six pack of em

On tap.  Huge head took forever to calm down.  Nothing special about the aroma. Light orange color with a bit of haze to it, white head which took a long time to calm. Very smooth taste, bit of sweetness and a number of flavors. Went down easy, no bitterness. Overall, great beer.

Not much aroma, but the beer has a deep orange look and a very rich flavor.  the high abv is noticeable as the beer is heavier than you might initially guess.  full of flavor though which is how great wheat beers should be. fantastic beer, but the 4 packs on sale are drastically overpriced
beer_name: Samuel Adams Imperial Series Imperial White
